SIMPLE: masticator
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Masticator
<hw>Mas"ti*ca`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who masticates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A machine for cutting meat into fine pieces for
toothless people; also, a machine for cutting leather, India rubber, or
similar tough substances, into fine pieces, in some processes of
manufacture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Masticatory</ent>⟦br⟧
